    "A simple AES BERT architecture, as depicted in Fig. 5, takes an essay text as an input and feeds it to the Transformer Encoder.",
    "Subsequently, BERT generates word embeddings for each token and a fixed-size representation of the entire script, denoted by [CLS].",
    "The [CLS] token encapsulates the comprehensive representation of the document as contextual word embeddings.",
    "By employing a fully connected linear layer (FC) with a sigmoid activation function, a score for a given essay can be predicted.",
    "Mayfield and Black (2020) investigated whether fine-tuning BERT leads to better performance compared to convolutional recurrent neural networks in AES tasks."
  ],
